rComments: Even thought I've started to take the course, the exams were pretty easy but writing the report was a little struggling though. But her accent is very good and she's always there to teach new stuff.
She was a great prof. One of the easiest classes I've ever taken. I would definitely recommend her as a prof as her lectures often end early. Her tests are very fair and the grading is clear.
Great professor and professional

Fun and easy class! Banaf is a very sweet lady and does care very much about your grade. She is open and happy to receive feedback. Class participation makes this class more fun. There is some work, but fast and easy to do.

A lot of weekly assignments but not a crazy amount of work - she tried really hard to help us understand the course material for our discipline course. Keep up with the weekly assignments and you'll do fine!

I had a mandatory discussion group as an accompaniment to this class. Read 2 books, 3 tests, 2 short papers. Her lectures themselves were fairly boring, and not very necessary to attend as the powerpoints were posted online and comprehensive of the entirety of the information presented. Very specific on rules but an easy class.
Cest une bonne professeure.

An average professor. I'll admit, her lectures can be really boring and she's not the most exciting lecturer. But, she is clear about grading and will let you know exactly what's on the exam. She is caring and very nice, but needs to improve her teaching skills.
She is excellent.
Good prof.
C'est une très bonne professeure. La matière est facile, mais elle l'a dit elle-même plusieurs fois que c'est un cours de français de base.

Very sweet lady, cares about her students. The class itself was pretty boring (mandatory basic french class) and showing up was not necessary for a decent grade. If you're looking for a simple class she is fine.
This was one of the easiest classes I've taken, you just have to write 2 texts and do a couple of grammar tests. The prof that I had was okay but you don't need to go to class, just the DGDs.
teacherRatingTags: ['Graded by few things', 'Clear grading criteria', 'Gives good feedback']

rComments: Si vous êtes un débutant en français, cette prof est pour vous. Par contre, la plupart des gens qui ont Karamifar, tels que moi-même, sont déjà assez avancés en français et se sentent dans un cours de niveau élémentaire. Elle s'y connait en français et s'exprime bien mais doit toujours se référer aux TA lorsqu'on lui pose des questions.
C'est une bonne professeure.
She seems new, but she is very nice and caring.
She is  caring and an amazing prof.

Although the fact that she seems like a very nice person, this course is terribly unorganized. I'm spending more time trying to figure out what she means than the actual content. Theories and researchers are not in order and her slides contradict themselves. I have never been so confused and lost in a course.

Her teaching is straightforward, but she closely (if not exactly) follows the textbook, and her slideshows are almost word-for-word. She spends quite a lot of time with doing book activities in-class rather than lecturing, which for some can be boring. Her assignments and exams are easy if you study a LOT.

I found this professor to be extremely disorganized. Though this class was supposed to be advanced level I in French, it felt like a beginner level course. She did not follow the syllabus at all. The class was great to get an easy A, but I learned absolutely nothing. She knows the French language quite well, but is terrible at teaching it.

I'm surprised by the positive reviews. I found her incredibly disorganized. She didn't seem to follow the syllabus and often appeared to improvise her lessons. No textbook was given and instead, she would often post a poorly scanned exert of a book. No clear instructions as to what will be found on the exam. No clear expectations for projects.
Excellent professor. She is very kind and teach clearly. One of the best courses I have ever had.
Very knowlageble professor. I enjoyed this course.
Very knowlagebale professor. I enjoyed this course and learned a lot.

I took this course with her, and I was impressed with all. She is very  knowledgeable. She paid attention to the students questions and use their feedbacks in the course material. In addition, she knows how to present great.

Seems new to teaching and is pretty disorganized. Cites Wikipedia in her powerpoints. Better off just reading the textbook and learning the material there, because she is no help. Tests questions are very specif, so study the details. Just a boring class, overall.
